,Recommended,296070,11842307,"Posted: 23 August, 2014",all,"SuperJer [Linux ""Hipster""]","Though I may sound a little critical, I am definitely recommending this game to those who like exploration, puzzle, and highly narrative games.  It may not appeal to everyone, but those who enjoy this type of game will find it worth their while, even if it is only a short while.As you can probably tell, this game has a strong narrative.  The story is well constructed, and is told very well.  It's not a groundbreaker, but it's easy to care about the character and his struggle.Gameplay-wise, this is a little mixed.  I definitely enjoyed it, though some of the puzzles could be frustrating.  Fairly often I found myself concentrating so hard on the puzzles, especially later in the game, that I had to consciously step back and take in the visuals and atmosphere.  This isn't necessarily good nor bad overall, but I personally would have preferred a little more journey and exploration, and a little less puzzle.  Nothing wrong with puzzles, but the game becomes fairly well saturated with them before long.  Also, when you're carrying things, which is often, they take up most of the screen, blocking out much of the breathtaking visuals.When navigating the terrain, you'll often collide for no apparent reason, but it's not so bad that it ruins anything.  You're always able to get to where you're going.All in all, I had fun playing the game.  Some may complain about how short it is, but I find the older I get, the less time I have to sit and complete something.  So these shorter games are very welcome additions to my library.  While it seems to lack some polish, you'll still look back once you've finished the game and deem it time well spent."
