,Recommended,296070,13175063,"Posted: 30 November, 2014",all,TheCrux,"Mind: Path to Thalamus is a puzzle game with a narrative. I was on the fence about buying it, as I thought it would be another ""walking simulator"" of just walking through a story line, but ended up buying it on a sale. (TL;DR pro/con list at the end)I was completely off on the ""just another walking simulator"" notion. The types of puzzles in this game are original, well thought out and progress in difficulty. There was only one puzzle near the end that I had to look up, but I was close and I would've gotten it with a bit more time. The puzzles involve four different ""areas"" where you can place an orb to accomplish something:- Night, which allows you to use gate ""portals"" to teleport to other ""portals"" and allows you to use a second orb that's only available in night ""mode""- Storm, which raises platforms to allow you to access higher areas or cross gaps- Past, which rebuilds broken structures- FogThe Scenery is amazing and almost every level is screenshot-worthy. I was really blown away with the visuals.Here's a list of pros and cons:Pros:- Amazing visuals- Pretty good story line- Original, fun puzzlesCons:- A couple puzzles may make you feel lost like you don't know what to do next. obviously it's a puzzle and it's expected, but I can think of one level that was somewhat large and I felt lost for a bit.- Somewhat short. Obviously playtimes will vary based on how fast someone can solve the puzzles, achievement hunting, looking at scenary, etc, but I was expecting more.tl;dr: Awesome game - unique and fun puzzles with a great story and narration, but somewhat short. If you're on the fence about this game, pick it up on sale."
