ebook to write stuff down and puzzles may take hours till youre able to solve em.the story in Mind is weird, the protagonist, which you are playing, is an idiot, a very annoying character. the protagonist is always talking to you, explaining you things and telling you about the past and future, so hes kinda talking to himself. but not only did his character annoy me, so did his voice. with every level ive got more and more annoyed of this♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥the game has absolutely no replayability at all and with the fact that the character annoyed me that much im quite happy that i never have to hear his voice again.ive paid 5€ for this game on sale, if i remember it correctly. the actual price for the game is 13€ which is by far too much. even 5€ is too much id pick this game up for 2-3€ if id be you, its not worth more. i think this game was created by artists and not game developers, at least thats how it feels. thats also the main reason why i just cant rate this game positive, the value for money is just purely bad and overweighs all positive aspects.another negative point is, no key bindings. theres only WASD and LMB/RMB used, but not all keyboard layouts have WASD on the same position and there are also lefthanded people which may be uncomfortable with those settings.so to sum it up; a very short beautiful game with a good atmosphere, non-challenging puzzles and absolutely no replaybility plus an annoying protagonist for an overpriced 13€."
