,Recommended,296070,13704601,"Posted: 29 December, 2014",all,TN Hoff,"This is an uncommonly gorgeous game - the art direction is fantastic.  The sheer scale of some of the things that happen in this game is breathtaking.  (Visually, this might be the best use of the Unreal engine I've ever seen.)  Without being too specific about the puzzles, once you figure out that backtracking is a thing, they strike a decent balance between fair and challenging - they're mostly fun and totally solvable if sometimes a bit cryptic.  The narrator is a prick - but I think that's part of the point.  He's a deeply flawed guy - and while the game's journey does represent a maturing process for him - he's still kind of a prick with loads of baggage.  It's as if he's searching too hard for meaning - calls himself out on it - and keeps doing it anyway.  If you can get past the imperfect character, the game is amazing - worth playing for the art direction and execution alone.  It may not be as polished as Portal 2 - but it's made by a much smaller team, and the artistic aspect of the game really knocks it out of the park.  If you like surrealism - this is for you.  Dive in, and get lost in another world.8/10 highly recommended."
