 obvious.6. The subtitles are too freaking small, out of sync, and sometimes jumbled and unreadable.7. I spent at least a quarter (if not a third) of my time in the game staring at a blank screen wondering if the game had crashed.8. I encountered very little music. Although, I must say I actually bought the game because of the music in the trailer, and when/where that music appears in the game I found very affecting.After a few hours it became obvious I was traipsing through some shmuck's inner psychological problems. Personally, I found that irritating. But that's just me. So I don't hold it against the game. What I do hold against the game is that I just didn't care about anything. I had no motivation to complete any puzzle, and completing a puzzle didn't give any reward I could discern.I bought the game at 75% off for $2.24. Essentially I bought it for that one piece of music. Don't buy this game if you're looking for some kind of story to motivate you and tie everything together. There isn't some great revelation at the end where ""everything suddenly makes sense.""Interesting puzles/mechanics. Poor execution. 1 awesome song."
