,Recommended,296070,14183688,"Posted: 26 January, 2015",all,M. Doucet,"There are some games where the actualgamecan get in the way of enjoying it. Sometimes Mind: Path to Thalamus is so damn beautiful that all you want to do is live in that world for awhile. I was worried that it might be similar to Kairo, with aggravatingly obscure puzzles, all style but no substance, but Mind stands out as a thoughtful and creative game. The logic puzzles here can be challenging, but at least your objectives are relatively clear. Where Mind suffers is in its storytelling, which seems more like an excuse for its lush environments to exist than anything as meaningful or profound as the game may want you to believe. The voice actor in particular (seen also in the Free To Play game Only If...) makes the ongoing monologue distracting at best.Thankfully the gorgeous design is enough to save the game, and the ""enhanced"" update brought even more thoughtful updates to the game. Also worth noting is that this game's achievements actually add to the gameplay and reward more detailed exploration. With its coming Oculus Rift update this game will be a must-have for those interested in the VR space. For the rest of us? Play it for the art and not the story.7/10."
